====Screen====

1) Measure the dimensions of the frame. 

2) Cut the frame into desired dimensions.

3) Use drill and screws to put together the frame. 

4) Cut out the screen into desired dimensions.

5) Staple the screen onto the frame. 

6) Attach the frame onto the body of the cold box using the drill and screws.

====Box====
1) Cut plywood into the dimensions from the measurements above. 

2) Use drill and screws to connect all boards together (the sides and bottom). 

3) For the shelves, measure and mark the side boards with a pencil to desired lengths. 

4) In addition, drill in the brackets where the marks are on the side boards. There should be 4 marks on each “side” board (two marks for each shelf).

5) Place the shelves into the box. 

6) Find the center of the top of the box by measuring and marking it.

7) For this top of the box, place onto two stands and clamp the "top" board onto these stands.

8) Use a bimetal hole saw that is attached with the drill to create the hole on this "top" board.

8) Attach the top onto the primary body of the cold box.

10) Then attach the vent onto the top of the cold box using the drill and screws.

11) Stain the cold box (optional).

====Insulation====
