==Operation==
Arrive on the top floor of the Campus Center for Appropriate Technology (CCAT) and ask the co-directors to go inside the house. In the kitchen is where the cold box will be. It is not installed at the moment; however, when it is installed, co-directors of CCAT can place produce onto the shelves. Note that the cold box works best when the outside temperatures are 65°F (18.3°C) or lower to achieve most effective cooling of the produce. 

===Maintenance===
The following components to maintain:
* Check if the pipe where the vent is located is leaking or not. If it is leaking, call CCAT directors for assistance.

* Check if the screen have any holes or damages. In addition, clean the screen from dust and bugs.

* Check for produce that are not in good condition and place old produce in the compost bin. 

* Monitor the temperatures of the cold box using a thermometer and record temperatures.

===Schedule===
Every week:
* check for unused or old produce.

Every two weeks:
* monitor and record temperatures inside the cold box.

Every month:
* clean the screen of the cold box. Possibly use a vacuum to clean the dust and bugs. 

* clean the pipe to rid of dust and bugs.

* check if there is a leak from the pipe where the vent will be.

